🔹 1. addBook()


Writes one record at the end of the file.


Time Complexity: O(1) (append operation)


Space Complexity: O(1)



🔹 2. displayBooks()


Reads all books sequentially.


Time Complexity: O(n)


Space Complexity: O(1) (only one object in memory at a time)



🔹 3. searchBook()


Linear search through file.


Time Complexity: O(n) (worst case: book at end or not found)


Space Complexity: O(1)



🔹 4. deleteBook()


Reads all records and rewrites except the deleted one.


Time Complexity: O(n)


Space Complexity: O(1) (uses temp file, not extra memory)



🔹 5. issueBook()


Searches and updates one record.


Time Complexity: O(n)


Space Complexity: O(1)



🔹 6. returnBook()


Same as issueBook.


Time Complexity: O(n)


Space Complexity: O(1)





